{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan an Nasai","section":{"0":""}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":352,"arabicnumber":352,"text":"It was narrated from 'Aishah that Umm Habibah asked the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) about bleeding. 'Aishah said:\"I saw her wash tub filled with blood.\" The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said to her: \"Stop (praying) for as long as your period used to last, then perform Ghusl","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":384.2,"arabicnumber":384.2,"text":"(Another chain) with similarity","grades":[],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":434.2,"arabicnumber":434.2,"text":"It was narrated from Tariq bin Shaihab that a man became Junub and did not pray. He came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and told him about that, and he said:\"You did the right thing.\" Then another man became Junub so he performed Tayammum and prayed. He came (to the Prophet (ﷺ)) who said to him what he had said to the other man- meaning, \"You did the right thing","grades":[],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":512,"arabicnumber":512,"text":"It was narrated from Salim, from his father, that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:\"The one who misses 'Asr prayer, it is as if he has been robbed of his family and his wealth.\" It was narrated from Ibn 'Umar that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: \"The one who misses 'Asr prayer, it is as if he has been robbed of his family and his wealth","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":570,"arabicnumber":570,"text":"It was narrated from Ibn Tawus that his father said:\"'Aishah, may Allah be please with her, said: 'Umar, may Allah be please with him, is not correct, rather the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) only prohibited, as he said: 'Do no deliberately seek to pray when the sun is rising or when it is setting, for it rises between the horns of a Shaitan","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":2821.2,"arabicnumber":2821.2,"text":"It was narrated that Ibn 'Abbas said:\"Zaid bin Arqam came and Ibn Abbas said to him, reminding him: \"What did you tell me about the game meat that was given to the Messenger of Allah when he was in Ihram?\" He said: \"Yes, a man gave him a piece of game meat but he returned it and said: 'We cannot eat it, we are in Ihram","grades":[],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3533.2,"arabicnumber":3533.2,"text":"Zainab said:\"Then I went into Zainab bint Jahsh when her brother died, and she called for some perfume and put some on. Then she said: 'By Allah, I do not have any need for perfume but I heard the Messenger of Allah say on the Minbar: It is not permissible for any woman who believes in Allah and the Last Day to mourn for anyone who dies for more than three days, except for a husband, (for whom the mourning period is) four months and ten days","grades":[],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3533.3,"arabicnumber":3533.3,"text":"Zainab said:\"I heard Umm Salamah say: 'A woman came to the Messenger of Allah and said: O Messenger of Allah, my daughter's husband has died and she has a problem in her eye; can I put kohl on her? The Messenger of Allah said: No. Then he said: It is four months and ten days. During the Jahiliyyah one of you would throw a piece of dung at the end of the year.'\" Humaid said: \"I said to Zainab: 'What is this throwing a piece of dung at the end of the year?' She said: 'If a woman's husband died, she would enter a small room (Hifsh) and wear her worst clothes, and she would not put on perfume or anything until a year. Then an animal would be brought, a donkey or sheep or bird, and she would end her 'Iddah with it (clean herself with it), and usually any animal used for that purpose would die. Then she would come out and would be given a piece of dung which she would throw, then she would go back to whatever she wanted of perfume, etc.'\" In the narration of Muhammad (bin Salamah) Malik said: Hifsh means hut","grades":[],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3722.2,"arabicnumber":3722.2,"text":"It was narrated from Zaid bin Thabit that the Prophet ruled that 'Umra (a gift given for life) belongs to the heir","grades":[],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3857,"arabicnumber":3857,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Daif Muquf"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Daif Muquf"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3858,"arabicnumber":3858,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih Maqtu"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Maqtu"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3859,"arabicnumber":3859,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih Maqtu"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Maqtu"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3860,"arabicnumber":3860,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih Isnaad Maqtu"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Isnaad Maqtu"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3861,"arabicnumber":3861,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih Isnaad Maqtu"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Isnaad Maqtu"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3862,"arabicnumber":3862,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Daif Isnaad"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Daif Isnaad"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3863,"arabicnumber":3863,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih Isnaad"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih Isnaad"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3864,"arabicnumber":3864,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":0,"hadith":0}},{"hadithnumber":3865,"arabicnumber":3865,"text":"","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghudda